      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Alternatively, if you open the class file in a hex editor you can look at bytes 7 and 8. The number will map to the numbers given in the above answer. E.g. <code>00 2E</code> -&gt; JDK 1.2 = 46 (0x2E hex). Useful if you don&#39;t have access to javap. ref: <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_class_file#General_layout\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_class_file#General_layout</a>"
