      "body" : "So I was working on a project that uses amazon sdk. The project uses Java 1.7. If I check inside of the <code>MANIFEST.MF</code> of amazon sdk it says <code>Build-Jdk: 1.8.0_111</code> , but if I use <code>javap -verbose MyClass | grep &quot;major&quot;</code> it says <code>major version: 50</code> which means Java Version 6. This is confusing. Does that mean - even though it was compiled with 8 but it can run on 6?"
